In [4]:
### lets build one dataframe each for trip, drive, and weather
Path = '../input/input_data/'
    
def consolidateFiles(sourceType:str,iterfiles:list):
    print(" ------  Consolidating for {} ------- ".format(sourceType))
    outDF = pd.DataFrame()
    for f_ in tqdm(iterfiles):
        outDF = pd.concat([outDF,pd.read_parquet(os.path.join(Path,'{}/{}'.format(sourceType,f_)))],0)
    return outDF
weatherDF = consolidateFiles('weather',weatherF)
weatherDF.head()

In [12]:
### create labels for temp, precipitation, windspeeds
weatherDF['templabels']=pd.cut(weatherDF['temperature_data'].astype(float),labels=['Low','Medium','High'],bins=3)
weatherDF['precplabels']=pd.cut(weatherDF['precipitation_data'].astype(float),labels=['Low','Medium','High'],bins=3)
weatherDF['windEWlabels']=pd.cut(weatherDF['wind_ew_data'].astype(float),labels=['Low','Medium','High'],bins=3)
weatherDF['windNSlabels']=pd.cut(weatherDF['wind_ns_data'].astype(float),labels=['Low','Medium','High'],bins=3)
In [13]:
for l_ in weatherDF['templabels'].unique():
    _ = weatherDF[weatherDF['templabels']==l_]
    sns.distplot(_['precipitation_data'].astype(float))
    plt.title("Distribution of precipitation for temperature label: {}".format(l_))
    plt.show()
